header.gameNote: MVC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINALS AT ST LOUIS MO

article.headline: Creighton 60, N. Iowa 57
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- Reserve Kenny Lawson scored 18 points and made a crucial putback in the final minute of Creighton's 60-57 victory over Northern Iowa on Friday in the quarterfinals of the Missouri Valley Conference tournament. Doug McDermott added 16 points and seven rebounds for fifth-seeded Creighton (19-13). Kwadzo Ahelegbe scored all but two of his 14 points in the second half for fourth-seeded Northern Iowa (19-13) but missed two shots in the final half-minute. Lawson followed Antoine Young's missed layup that rolled out with 27 seconds to go for the game's final points. Young added 11 points and seven assists for two-time defending champion Northern Iowa, which never led. Lawson was 4-for-5 from 3-point range to match his career high. Jake Koch had 15 points and Anthony James 10 for Northern Iowa, but the losers were just 1-for-4 from the free throw line while Creighton went 8-for-10.
